'''{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}'''是一家对时事和其它新闻报道提供[[戏仿|戏仿]]评论的[[英国|英国]][[讽刺|讽刺]][[网站|网站]]。《[[星期日泰晤士報|星期日泰晤士報]]》前时政记者尼尔·拉弗蒂（{{lang|en|Neil Rafferty}}）和《[[苏格兰人报|苏格兰人报]]》前财经版编辑保罗·斯托克斯（{{lang|en|Paul Stokes}}）于2007年创办了这家网站，并且留任主编。两人都通过网站的广告和商品赚取收入，还会聘请[[自由撰稿人|自由撰稿人]]。网站上发表的文章以其[[超现实主义幽默|荒诞]]、[[厕所幽默|粪便式]]的幽默和有见地的政治讽刺获得了好评，被认为与美国的《[[洋葱报|洋葱报]]》相比也毫不逊色。

== 历史 ==
{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}于2007年4月由保罗·斯托克斯和尼尔·拉弗蒂两位[[记者|记者]]创立。斯托克斯曾是《苏格兰人报》的财经版编辑，并且也为《苏格兰周日报》（{{lang|en|Scotland on Sunday}}）和《{{link-en|每日记录|Daily Record (Scotland)}}》写文章。拉弗蒂曾担任《星期日泰晤士報》的时政记者，他还为《{{link-en|新闻协会|Press Association}}》和《商业{{lang|en|AM}}》创作稿件，并且是前烟民游说团体{{lang|en|[[FOREST|FOREST]]}}的发言人。<ref name="the Free Society">{{cite web |last=Rafferty |first=Neil |archivedate=2010-01-28 |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2010-01-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100128110739/http://www.thefreesociety.org/Columnists/Neil-Rafferty/new-labour-and-the-bully-state |url=http://www.thefreesociety.org/Columnists/Neil-Rafferty/new-labour-and-the-bully-state |title=Forget the nanny state, welcome to the bully state |date=2008-02-06 |publisher=''The Free Society'' }}</ref>。该网站最初的灵感来自美国讽刺出版物《洋葱报》，斯托克斯和拉弗蒂看到了[[英国|英国]]讽刺出版物的市场差距<ref name="independent">{{cite web |last=Luckhurst |first=Tim |archivedate=2012-10-25 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025182323/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/the-daily-mash--satirical-scatological-and-already-profitable-899541.html |title=The Daily Mash - satirical, scatological and already profitable |publisher=''The Independent'' |date=2008-08-17 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/the-daily-mash--satirical-scatological-and-already-profitable-899541.html }}</ref><ref name="allmedia">{{cite web |archivedate=2008-10-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081012025802/http://www.allmediascotland.com/articles/1172/20042007/give_us_this_day_our_daily_mash |url=http://www.allmediascotland.com/articles/1172/20042007/give_us_this_day_our_daily_mash |title=Give us, This Day, our Daily Mash |publisher=''All Media Scotland'' |date=2007-04-20 |accessdate=2009-02-06 }}</ref>。两位记者主要都是为[[苏格兰|苏格兰]]报社工作，{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}有时会专业针对苏格兰及其文化<ref name="allmedia" /><ref name="thelist">{{cite web |url=http://film.list.co.uk/article/14906-the-hot-100-2008/ |title=The Hot 100 2008 |publisher=''The List'' |date=2008-12-11 (updated 2009-01-06) |accessdate=2013-10-02 |archivedate=2013-04-20 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130420022009/http://film.list.co.uk/article/14906-the-hot-100-2008/ }}</ref>。

斯托克斯和拉弗蒂从网站上获得了收入，并带领了一小队[[自由職業|自由職業]]作家。网站通过[[廣告|廣告]]和[[产品|产品]]赚取收入，已经成为一个获利颇丰的成功企业。网站明显以上班族为目标观众，为广告商提供了利基机会<ref name="independent" />。[[花旗集团|花旗集团]]的雇员曾向{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}和独立出版物报怨公司已经禁止他们访问该网站<ref name="times">{{cite web |last=Waller |first=Martin |url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/columnists/article5562595.ece |title=The Daily Mash bash is, sadly, no laughing matter for Citi |publisher=''The Times'' |date=2009-01-22 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612161140/http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/columnists/article5562595.ece |archivedate=2011-06-12 |deadurl=no }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。网站第一年发表的重点文章已经集结成书出版，书名为《{{lang|en|Halfwit Nation: Frontline Reporting from the War on Stupid}}》（意译为：《笨蛋国家：愚蠢战争的前线报告》）<ref name="thelist" />，该书一方面受到好评<ref>{{cite web |last=Ivison |first=John |url=http://www.nationalpost.com/opinion/story.html?id=9ac1c7e4-ee5c-40fd-ad0a-c57c5ce1eed6 |title=Near death cures Tories ''National Post'' |date=2009-01-07 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131002145305/http://www.nationalpost.com/opinion/story.html?id=9ac1c7e4-ee5c-40fd-ad0a-c57c5ce1eed6 |archivedate=2013-10-02 }}</ref>，另一方面也受到缺乏才智，幽默过于粗俗的批评<ref>{{cite web |last=Hickson |first=Ella |url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/why-can-t-we-have-more-good-old-fashioned-fun-this-christmas-asks-ella-hickson-1-1151156 |title=Why can't we have more good, old-fashioned fun this Christmas |publisher=''The Scotsman'' |date=2008-12-13 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |archive-date=2013-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215457/http://www.scotsman.com/news/why-can-t-we-have-more-good-old-fashioned-fun-this-christmas-asks-ella-hickson-1-1151156 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

一项2008年进行的网上调查显示，这个网站的读者主要包括阅读《[[獨立報|獨立報]]》、《[[衛報|衛報]]》和《[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]》的[[大學|大學]][[畢業|毕业生]]。其中65%的年收入在3万[[英镑|英镑]]以上，22%的年收入超过7万英镑，网站81%的点击率来自英国用户，19%来自[[美国|美国]]。<ref name="independent" />

== 反响 ==
{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}提供对时事和其它新闻报导的戏仿评论，被称为英国首屈一指的讽刺新闻网站<ref name="independent" /><ref name="howdo">{{cite news |title=Mansized w00t!media feasts on The Daily Mash |publisher=''How Do'' |date=2008-06-10}}</ref>。网站“讽刺起来无畏无私”，旨在提供与主流讽刺相比不那么政治正确的幽默<ref name="independent" />。网站的幽默还曾获得过诸如“残酷”、“粪便般”、“荒谬”和“无礼”的评价<ref name="independent" /><ref name="telegraph">{{cite web |archivedate=2012-07-22 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722204953/http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/finance/financialcrisishumour/5394237/Bastard_Americans_ruin_your_life_Top_5_Daily_Mash_financial_crisis_satires/ |url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/finance/financialcrisishumour/5394237/Bastard_Americans_ruin_your_life_Top_5_Daily_Mash_financial_crisis_satires/ |title='Bastard Americans ruin your life': Top 5 Daily Mash financial crisis satires |publisher=''The Daily Telegraph'' |date=2008-10-07 |accessdate=2013-10-02 }}</ref>。{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}被认为是美国出版物《洋葱报》在英国的替代品和新兴的竞争对手，其覆盖面与后者相比毫不逊色，并且在有些情况下还被认为要优于后者<ref name="independent" /><ref name="times" /><ref name="howdo" /><ref name="telegraph" /><ref name="gwg">{{cite web |url=http://www.thegoodwebguide.co.uk/news-info/websites/news/the-daily-mash/4897 |title=The Daily Mash |publisher=''The Good Web Guide'' |accessdate=2013-10-02 |archivedate=2013-09-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921062829/http://www.thegoodwebguide.co.uk/news-info/websites/news/the-daily-mash/4897 }}</ref>。除了其中的幽默外，网站还有时被认为很有见地<ref name="independent" /><ref name="times" /><ref name="telegraph" />。一些评论家指出，并非所有该网站上的文章都在讽刺方面获得了成功，与其它讽刺作品相比，其内容缺乏语言上的创新<ref name="independent" /><ref name="telegraph" /><ref name="gwg" />。

{{lang|en|The Daily Mash}}上的故事有时会得到其它出版物的评论。获得好评的戏仿覆盖范围包括[[杰里米·克拉克森|杰里米·克拉克森]]旨在针对[[戈登·布朗|戈登·布朗]]并得到广泛宣传的攻击性言论<ref>{{cite web |last=Massie |first=Alex |url=http://www.spectator.co.uk/alexmassie/3329761/dubious-proposition-of-the-day.thtml |title=Dubious Proposition Of The Day |accessdate=2011-06-05 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2011-06-05 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605080113/http://www.spectator.co.uk/alexmassie/3329761/dubious-proposition-of-the-day.thtml |publisher=''The Spectator'' |date=2009-02-06 }}</ref>，[[2008年夏季奥林匹克运动会英国代表团|大不列颠代表团]]奖牌获得者的广告交易<ref>{{cite web |last=Waller |first=Martin |archivedate=2011-06-12 |url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/columnists/article4636655.ece |title=British Airways out of the medals in PR race |publisher=''The Times'' |date=2008-08-30 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612112837/http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/columnists/article4636655.ece }}{{subscription required}}</ref>，[[北岩银行|北岩银行]]的{{link-en|北岩银行国有化|nationalisation of Northern Rock|国有化}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Goodley |first=Simon |archivedate=2012-11-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111064903/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2816131/Business-Diary-FSA-fixer-Sir-Callum-could-be-between-Rock-and-a-new-place.html |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2816131/Business-Diary-FSA-fixer-Sir-Callum-could-be-between-Rock-and-a-new-place.html |title=Business Diary: FSA fixer Sir Callum could be between Rock and a new place |publisher=''The Telegraph'' |date=2007-09-21 |accessdate=2013-10-02 }}</ref>，戈登·布朗与[[本篤十六世|教皇]]见面<ref>{{cite web |last=Campbell |first=David |url=http://www.citywire.co.uk/new-model-adviser/citywires-best-of-the-web/a330231 |title=Citywire's Best of the Web |publisher=''Citywire'' |date=2009-02-20 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2012-03-05 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305055438/http://www.citywire.co.uk/new-model-adviser/citywires-best-of-the-web/a330231 }}</ref>和{{link-en|银行家奖金|bankers' bonuses}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Marshall |first=Chris |archivedate=2012-03-05 |url=http://www.citywire.co.uk/new-model-adviser/citywires-best-of-the-web/a329223 |title=Citywire's Best of the Web |publisher=''Citywire'' |date=2009-02-11 |accessdate=2013-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305055449/http://www.citywire.co.uk/new-model-adviser/citywires-best-of-the-web/a329223 }}</ref>。

